1 (11) To be informed verbally and in writing, in a developmentally appropriate and
2 trauma-responsive manner, as to why a specific request for communication or visitation with
3 a sibling has been limited, denied or prohibited.
4 [(11)] (12) To have the rights under this section apply regardless of whether the parental rights
5 of one or more of the foster child’s parents have been terminated, as safe and appropriate.
